  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support Cluster Response to Drought-Affected Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs), through Monitoring IDPs Inflow and Outflow, as well as Intention Survey, in Herat and Badghis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to critical levels of internal displacement in Afghanistan caused by what is being described as the worst drought in the country indecades, through this action IOM&#x2019;s Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) will continue to implement flow monitoring to identify and register the newly arriving drought-affected internally displaced persons (IDP) caseload in Herat City, as well as in Qala-e-Naw in Badghis. In addition, IOM will share the information with humanitarian partners to facilitate onward registration of newly arriving IDPs into humanitarian assistance programmes and expedite subsequent delivery of assistance. Additionally, DTM will also continue to track the outflow of IDPs returning to their places of origin or into secondary displacement as well as conduct return intention surveys in locations of displacement toidentify the intentions, motivations, needs and concerns. This will enable partners to better integrate the concerns and requirements of potential returnees into return packages and into return strategies in areas of origin to deliver sustainable return solutions.</narrative>
  </description>
